    <text id="B0312T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell points out an error in Jackson's reporting procedures.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. &amp;
                        A.L.</abbr><lb/>Head <abbr expan="Quarters">Qrs.</abbr> 9th Sub <abbr
                            expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. Thos. P. Jackson<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                        >A.S.A.C.</abbr><lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-02-03"><abbr expan="February">Feby</abbr> 3/68</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your attention is invited to an error occuring in your "Property cases tried by
                    Civil Authorities" for the last three or four months. Said Report is called for
                    by Circular No. 10 Series 1866, <abbr expan="Headquarters">HdQrs</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner, Virginia">Asst Comr Va</abbr>. You
                    invariably make said report as required by Circular No. 6 - Circular no. 6 is
                    the circular requiring a report of Bureau affairs. Please avoid this error in
                    future.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obedt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">St</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
